[Maybe and maybe not ..... Oncologists all have their routine before, during and after treatment so it's really up to him/her., Considering all the other issues one more scan would be far down on the worry list., I'm sure you will be having them after treatment and perhaps routinely for a period of time., Usually there are yearly check-ups with Onc., or possibly 6 months at first when you have finished treatment., Some Oncologists see patients for a couple of years and some will see the patient as long as the patient wishes., It's a very individual thing with the Oncologists., Just hang in there; you know it won't be over in a moment .... all things take time and we all have a problem being patient when it comes to WAITING., Do you best, you've done a SUPER job so far; don't spoil your record .... Take care now.]
