[You are welcome Joanne, I don't think it's a cyst either,I just mentioned that some cysts could also look suspicious., What you have is most probably a Fibroadenoma which is a solid lump that needs to be biopsied to make sure that in fact it is a benign lesion,which could also present with calcification and not well circumcised ., Many breast lumps that need to be investigated are not necessarily malignant but  the only way to make sure is to have a biopsy., Hoping that all turns out fine for you! :)]
