['341516443', '1197063641', '869120893', '816484406', '8671826912']
{'HIF2016_DIS02': {'651514332': Hi, Breast cysts can be classified as either simple or complex., '1308334390': Simple Cysts (fluid filled sacs) have virtually no chance of containing malignancy; they do not need to be aspirated unless they are too large and causing discomfort., '1700511941': However a complex cyst is more concerning because it will on occasion be an intracystic cancer., '1448128037': These type of cysts are also fluid filled sacs but contain a good percentage of solid elements, like old blood or debris., '1046850526': Usually complex cysts are aspirated and the cells examined under the microscope to better evaluate their nature and to rule out cancer., '2108873182':  A fine needle aspiration is a simple procedure and you shouldn’t be scared because the site to be biopsied will be numbed with a local anesthetic., '1061058322': Please take my advice and call your Doctor to reschedule the FNA biopsy ASAP so you can have peace of mind., '1159907466': Believe me, knowing what’s going on is much better than not knowing and worrying about it needlessly., '1773141681': Best wishes.., '1706106055': If you aren't willing to follow your Doctor's advice regarding the necessary testing we cannot offer any further help or advice for you here., '767391713': Best wishes and we truly hope that your issue is not a serious one ....., '1834068674': Hi, thanks for quick reply.... i understand what you say &amp; will follow it.... I just want to know is it still compulsory for fnac coz now i dont have any lumps &amp; pain..., '257515149': Unless you have had another Ultrasound test there is no way for you to know whether you have the same lump or not., '1905944761': Obviously you are still not willing to do as your Doctors have advised since you seem to be coming up with any excuse not to have the recommended biopsy., '275053332': We are here to help women who are also willing to help themselves and do their part in their health care., '795261213':  Best wishes., '2040188263': Hi, Not all breast lumps are palpable, but they can certainly be seen when you have an Ultrasound test., '599516619': Japdip has already advised you that if your Radiologist recommended a biopsy, you should, by all means, follow his/her advice ASAP to make sure that there is nothing serious., '59951661911': Believe me that you will feel much better knowing what this lump represents than not knowing., '1433205206': Take care.., '2033144643': Not even a Radiologist can tell you anything for sure until you have the biopsy and the cells examined by a Pathologist., '390086057': This lump could be anything and not necessarily breast cancer., '709687145': Please understand that we are not doctors and if we can't answer your questions it's because we simply don't know what else to say except to have the biopsy., '547396458': Right side came back as invasive grade 2., '1534990510': Waiting for left side results., '753525109': Hi, I am so sorry to hear about your diagnosis., '1093793583': I know finding out that we have breast cancer is scary and overwhelming but don’t be discouraged., '1865506768': Breast cancer is a treatable disease since new technologies and many advanced treatments are available these days., '24989539': Your team of Doctors will plan treatments designed specifically for you and hopefully they will be successful in achieving complete recovery., '1308037340': Hoping that the biopsy done on your left breast will result in benign findings., '1773395385': Best wishes…, '306911752': Please let us know if you need anything., '1539687104':  Zouzi , thank you for giving such wonderful support to rumpled and all your members on the community., '37707997': Your friends at MedHelp, Cheryl, '1650221801': I am so sorry about your diagnoses., '1280269948':  I know how scary it is, and how alone you can feel., '592340413':  Please know you are being thought of., '666306322':   Your doctors will come up with a great plan, and you will beat this!, '725394286':   As I have been told more than once "Fight Like A Girl!"., '1371019640':  Hugs!!!, '569155981': Thank you Cheryl for your kind acknowledgment., '2007448578': It is very appreciated! :), '752281920': I really hope "rumpled" will be just fine once her treatments start., '1410607360': Hi and thank you for the update., '815642281': It’s rather unusual to have cancer in both breasts, but unfortunately it can occur and I am really sorry that this happened to you., '960433479': Even if you are one of the few women to experience cancer bilaterally, the scenario isn't as dire as it sounds., '1423803463': Many studies have shown that a woman's prognosis is not necessarily worse if she has breast cancer in both breasts, and that the outcomes in such cases are often excellent., '888965391': Although each breast may require a different treatment strategy, the overall treatment for breast cancer in both breasts is no different than for cancer that occurs in just one breast., '180248256': The good thing is that the tumor in your right breast is rather small and is ER/PR positive which will respond well to medication, such as Tamoxifen or other similar drugs to lower considerably the risk of recurrence., '894201732': The tumor in your left breast is Grade 1 which is also a good thing., '818386018': It’s going to be a long journey but don’t be disheartened., '655754989': Take one step at a time, follow your Doctor’s recommendation and I am sure you’ll be able to beat this disease like many of us did., '319088625': Wishing you all the best and successful outcome., '1674073552': Hi, ER (Estrogen) and PR (Progesterone) receptor status tests are done to show whether or not one or both of those hormones fuel your tumor., '56016538': Estrogen positive, even if it’s weak, medication such as Tamoxifen (or other similar drugs) is usually recommended to lower the risk of recurrence in the same breast and helps prevent new cancer in the opposite breast., '2117673992':  Cancer that is hormone-sensitive is slightly slower growing and has a better chance of responding to hormone-suppression drugs, than cancer that is hormone receptor negative., '1310647909':  HER-2/neu negative cancer is also a good thing, because it is considered less aggressive than HER-2 positive., '2091279072':  I am sure that your Doctors will explain all this to you in details, when you’ll meet them., '357286565':  Since you have decided on a double mastectomy, I will send you a link by PM., '1748854575': Wishing you all the best and I hope that everything goes smoothly for you., '14332052062': Take care.., '369657961': Hi  I just did a follow up ultra sound, on a lump that my radiologist had been following for a year and a half., '1094484228':  My results said that it grew and changed from 5mm to 9mm diagnoses bi raids 4  so i had the biopsy doctor calls and said that tissues are benign., '699794779':   Then he proceeds to tell me that i have a intraductal papilloma 9mm., '604850318':  he then stated that i need and excisional biopsy  time to see a breast surgent,  during the conversation he stated that it is very rare that these are cancer only a 5% chance., '1008018793':   So my questions is can i leave this alone i prefer to just follow it?, '1895255908':   If i left it in and it did turn to cancer what could the outcome be how dangerous could it get even if i am being followed., '1790446210':    I again would prefer to just leave it alone., '296676229':  Thank you., '591027433': I would NOT just leave it alone and I can't imagine why anyone would choose to do this., '1092709910': 5% may not seem much of a chance to you but even a 1% chance would send me to a Breast Surgeon immediately., '1569487267': You can do whatever you feel comfortable with but since there has been growth give it some more thought before you decide to ignore this condition., '536793672': Even if you do see a Breast Surgeon there is a chance that he/she may agree with waiting and doing close interval testing and