: Thank you!, '290521272': It sounds as though you have found a GREAT Surgeon who has exactly the right information and caring that you need., '355276762': The follow-up plan seems very appropriate and I would be comfortable with that myself., '1660980221': I do think it wise to go ahead with the second opinion to further clear things in your mind., '2137316482': The hematoma issue isn't at all unusual in such circumstances with biopsies but it can complicate the situation., '1144677266': Remember that the decision you make today or 3 months from now won't necessarily change the outcome., '1055770250': Even though papilloma can be cancer, if there is only one they are usually watched for a period of time., '893162685': You're on the right track but try not to confuse yourself by doing TOO much research as no 2 cases are the same and you can't depend too much on percentages, they are too general., '809780317': Take care and stay busy .... NO negative thinking !!, '1690285322': Hi I went for my second opinion, Not sure what to make of the appointment though., '1495894517': This doctor is a top breast Sergent in my area, She actually did my first breast surgery in 2008., '1120336500':   When i saw her i felt like she was a little pushy,  She said to me it grew and surgery  was the best route even though i do not have any of the symptoms and the biopsy came back benign., '1641269773': She quoted to me (Pathology report too consider excision.), '1455101857': When i ask questions i felt like she thought i was stupid and she did not want to answer questions she cut me off, proceeded to tell me two options surgery or follow every six months., '549740687':  My question which i think is important does anyone know?, '806168849': Are there any studies of women who were follow with intraductal papilloma what is the long term out come., '426713677': That's too bad that you had a less than comfortable experience with the Breast Surgeon; perhaps she was having a bad day ????, '514655684': At this point since the chance of a single papilloma being malignant is rather small you might as well follow it for the recommended 6 months., '214807745': This all began the last of November and you should count the 6 months from that date and see what is recommended at your next check-up which would be in the Spring., '2136290454': If at that time it is determined to be benign then it can be left alone., '888451255': On the other hand if you are "done" with all the re-checks and possible biopsies then have it removed and over with., '97086927': It all comes down to what you are comfortable with., '192197947': I would make my appointment now for the 6 month check-up if that's the way you intend to go so there will be no waiting when the time actually arrives., '1592200492':  Regards ...., '1861139192': I really don't see any difference in the two., '705877977': The area is being removed either way., '1574037539': It seems to me that this is just the use of different terminology., '52737556':  Best wishes for a speedy recovery ....., '2081141412': That does seem rather a long time but it depends upon exactly what your normal activity consists of, like strenuous exercise which would not be wise or several other things that would  put undue strain on muscles, etc., '595270619': I would increase your activities very gradually but NEVER go against the advice of the Surgeon., '374639454': Complete healing of the tissues does take quite some time and you certainly would not want to delay that., '1370111683':  I'm glad to hear the things went well and hope for GREAT news when the reports come in., '357026958': Do take it easy though.... Regards., '1856706048': When I went in for my mammogram, I was told that my benign scattered calcifications that I had for the last 2 years were misread and are actually fine, linear calcifications, but because they were stable for 2 years they told me to come back in 6 months., '1113876556':  They gave me a BI RADS 3., '1181561008':  When I got my report, my breast density was reported as extremely dense., '247194292':  I have always had heterogeneously dense breasts., '591339982':  I have since done a lot of googling and cannot understand why they wouldn't biopsy., '1712694390':  I have found out that DCIS can be stable for a while and that the morphology is more important than the stability over time., '1506275081':  Why would they wait!, '130590630':  I am so scared!, '192907486':  Do they know what they are doing?, '911976719': Thoughts please?, '795942794': Hi., '1728031891':  Experienced Radiologists are quite able to identify typically benign breast calcifications depending on their form and pattern., '396543077': If no suspicion is detected a biopsy is not required to prevent unnecessary procedures., '1297218234':  BIRADS Category 3, means that the findings have a very high probability of being benign, therefore  recommending a short-interval follow-up., '1548623475': I wouldn't worry so much if I were you, because what your radiologist has recommended is standard procedure., '365160667': If these calcification were suspicious in any way, I am sure a biopsy would have certainly been ordered., '1724281747':  But of course this is up to you to decide….if you still feel uncomfortable waiting six months for a follow up, you could always have your films read by another Radiologist for a second opinion, or ask your Doctor to order a biopsy., '867182691':  Best wishes...  , '246137679': Thank you for your answer., '994107068':  I don't understand why I have to have a mammogram in 6 months., '1677336066':  Why can't I just get one in 1 year?, '1574494696':  I don't think BI RADS 3 is very useful to have to spend the extra money to watch something that is benign., '1681805608':  When will I ever go back to once a year mammograms?, '1230290186': Hi again, You have been asked to have these calcification monitored every 6 month simply because when the radiologist assigns calcifications to a "probably benign" category, the risk of malignancy even if very low ( less than 2%) can change unexpectedly., '431371336': Typically these calcifications will be monitored every six months for at least one year., '351295205': Assuming that no new changes are found, your doctor will recommend you have a routine mammogram once a year., '171623310': I hope that you’ll follow your doctor’s recommendation to make sure there is no change in the size, shape or number of calcifications., '1,43321E+11': Take care.., '1678936428': My calcifications have already been stable for over 2 years., '2003899890':  Can you show me any resource that says if a radiologist sees fine, linear calcifications to "wait and see" for six months?, '1483380640':   If they want them stable for a year, I have been stable for more than 2 years., '329263696':  I have not seen 1 resource where it is recommended that fine, linear calcifications be put in the BI RADS 3 or 2 categories., '1099817452':  My mammograms have all been the same, the only difference is that the radiologists have misread them., '2966762292':  Thank you, '1818710939': If the calcifications can change unexpectedly, then is the risk still less than 2%?, '102130753':  If they haven't changed in 2 years, what is the risk they will change in 2 1/2 years, 3 years, ect...?, '1501818390': I really cannot say why your Radiologist asked you to follow-up in 6 months since your calcifications have been stable for 2 years., '1372066530': Linear calcification is not always indicative of malignancy., '286367704': The suspicion is raised only when they are clustered and appear to form several branches., '1569854859': When they are linear but detached, such as probably yours are, it’s usually not worrisome but they have to be monitored regularly., '2092426263': I wish I could give you more information about the things you are requesting here, but the only advice I can give you is to have your Mammogram films read by a different Radiologist for a second opinion and also to have your test report explained to you in details by your Doctor who is your best source of information., '2140302557': I wish you well...  , '1867518096': Thank you zouzi for the information., '1529609706':  I don't understand if they are not worrisome, why watch them?, '1980048256':  It seems like a waste of resources., '1716923313':  What benign condition is linear but detached calcifications?, '695798262': It appears from the many posts on this forum regarding incisions opening after lumpectomies that it must be pretty common., '301594413':  I had a lumpectomy on March 12., '1099188297':  Two weeks later, it opened overnight., '1718632296':  In the morn it was oozing & bleeding., '1601156060':  I returned to the surgeon, who said it was infected., '288128148':  I was given antibiotics., '1750831443':  My oncologist looked at it a week later and said it was no longer infected, but to return to the surgeon if it looked like it wasn't healing., '1624972942':  Part of the incision is slowly healing, but a new section opened and is bleeding slightly., '596685493':  I keep it covered with gauze to keep it clean., '77860423':  How long shoud I give this to heal?, '3,11295E+11': Thanks., '253848826':  I didn't expect this to happen at all with the healing of the incision., '328647200':  My surgeon did not seem concerned., '577982755':  He surely sees it all the time., '1700127094':  It's good to be reassured., '629089878':  I am so glad to have this site with all who care so much about one another., '89858213':   So it's been about a month or so since the wound opened., '1883986361':  That part seems to be healing., '317647290':  There is another section that after all this time, that decided to open the other day., '2117455694':  It's small and bleeding just a little., '687646330':  I'll give it some more time., '1257111547':  Thank you again and I hope everything is ok with you now., '1828899364': I didn't either., '1236303866':  Personally I didn't expect to get an infection and definitely didn't anticipate needing district nursing input., '1443703862': Perhaps I took recovery for granted as I healed really well, and quickly, after having a duct out during a previous operation., '800520470': It is good if a surgeon doesn't seem concerned -I think., '1978660194': Bleeding is a good sign as it denotes healthy tissue., '1438349473':  Too much bleeding is not though., '1625119573': I've really benefited from this site and the support, advice and information too., '282012432':  It's been invaluable., '1381856024': I expect that section too will heal., '384393901':  I think it's normal for us to become anxious, etc during our recoveries., '480707123':  This is all new to us and we're learning about ourselves and our bodies during this process., '1326558710': I had stitches poke through my skin too., '1068673054':  Just when I thought I'd healed I found this thing on my breast., '368972932':  I was scared it had become infected again but it was only a mushy little stitch which I pulled out myself., '898638523':  (The stitch was redundant anyhow as the surgical registrar had cut it to insert a drain for the infection)., '2016899921': You're welcome., '582840957':   I'm fine., '1655701829':  I've just finished radiation treatment and are getting over residual fatigue., '917490958': Just be vigilant about your breast (without making it worse) and discuss any concerns you have with your doctor., '23402': J, '371382612': A related discussion, <a href="/posts/Breast-Cancer/post-lumpectomy-/show/2678465">post lumpectomy </a> was started., '2137068100': Hello., '346028708':  I am having the same problem., '1589929095': My wound is still open after 5 weeks., '1831096411':  I have to and see surgeon on Monday and likely have it packed and changed daily she said., '285790521':  This *****!!!., '1402436785':  My radiation has been delayed by several weeks they said until healed., '1378388681':  My question is, does it hurt to have packing., '1633772740':  I have never had it before and am a little overwhelmed, '936023860': This is a very old thread., '623550510': I would suggest you start your own new  thread., '755177697': If you describe the details of your situation and ask your questions there, you will be more likely to get answers addressed specifically to you and your concerns., '219896547': Best wishes, '1872969565': Radiation does delay healing so that's why you are being delayed for that part of your treatment., '538952223': As far as the packing is concerned, if the area isn't painful at the present then I doubt that it will be terribly uncomfortable., '1562509636': I have had a couple of areas that required packing and I had no pain but it was not in the same area as yours., '859134688': The amount of discomfort with the packing and removing it daily would also depend on the depth of the wound., '247629535':  Here's hoping it will be effective and not cause you very much discomfort., '1202164928': Hang in there, these things do happen now and then but they can be overcome with a little extra time., '175042842':   Kindest regards ...., '42338658': I had a 3D mammo because of a large mass in my right breast., '1789855975':  I was told a 3D is much more accurate than a standard mammo., '782339731':  Nobody would tell me the result of this but now they say I need an ultrasound., '1468390945':  If the 3D is so accurate why would they need an ultrasound?, '1387240668':  That means cancer,right?, '2124384404':  Nobody willtellme anything and I amso scared., '1939534655': I am terrified and confused and cannot remember the many,many things I have been told in the last few days and that includes posts here., '1106276103':  But you are wrong -- no one has been "more than happy" to explain things., '2102226916':  The medical professionals have not been forthcoming, they have been elusive and reluctant which leads me to believe they are hiding something very bad., '788824448': I see no reason to panic at this point., '1183469667': MRI is a much more sensitive type of test and can often show things that other tests do not., '537495848': A biopsy of course is the only sure way to diagnose what this mass represents., '1138897396': It could be a Fibroadenoma which is a benign breast tumor., '956023719': I would be surprised that a mass of this size representing cancer would not have shown up on either the Mammogram or Ultrasound., '1274196465': Proceed with the recommended biopsy which will define more accurately what you're dealing with., '1074178099': Being terrified never helps and usually tends to cloud your vision as well as your thoughts., '943078707': I imagine that you are seeing a Breast Specialist but if not this is something that you need to arrange., '1832094990': Family history accounts for a very small percentage of diagnosed cases of Breast Cancer even though it is a risk factor., '2,11358E+11':   Regards ....., '1107066438': Thanks so much for helping me down off of the ledge., '964568750': It has become all consuming., '1901909897':  Biopsy is on Thursday., '905794881': Wish me luck!, '1297728127': You're more than welcome .... it's scary up there on the ledge :) Luck, Wishes and Prayers are with you from all of us here., '1955506531': We know how it is but whatever it is we always seem to be able to handle it., '526674840':   Let us know when you get your results.... Regards, '1171927058': Thanks for the update .... sounds as though you have done well so far and it's a GREAT thing that nodes were not involved., '1970631378': As far as the Chemo goes, it's hard to say., '1577134038': Everyone and their response to the drugs is so varied you'll just have to wait and see .... great advice, right ??, '1809654519': Seriously, some women can breeze through it with little or no problem and others have adverse reactions., '1721938714': Keep positive thoughts and don't go looking for "what might occur" and don't hesitate to make clear any problems you may have., '710311338': The Oncology team will have many things that will help with or counteract any side effects that you experience., '2079986640': Don't keep it to yourself; make it known if you have a problem of any kind., '1172850370': Wishing you a good experience during your treatment .... you can do it, I know you can !!, '1057348614':  Take care and keep us posted when you have the time., '17504284222':    Kindest regards ...., '1223457183': Trying g to keep positive, but it is quite hard at times., '1058168520': Do you think I'll be needing a petscan before chemo?, '2086925072': Breast doc says no., '984331207': We will see what the oncologist says., '526373795': I am really not up for any more scans at this point., '814051225': Just want to deal with the matter at hand and get it over with., '2103016052': Thanks for the kind words., '701155170': Is 3 weeks post op a long time before seeing the oncologist?, '1884016871': I'm hearing no because you need time to heal., '1826099422': WAiting and being anxious really *****!, '1102058022': No, not at all .... healing is a complicated process in the tissues below the surface., '1711536123': There will seem to be no end to the "waiting" but it's all a learning experience., '1301532863': After all is said and done you will be a much more patient person ..... hopefully  :) ., '1550914536':   take care ....., '515189796': Hi, Please try not to panic!, '2141073585': Most breast lesions are not cancerous., '12453627212': A variety of benign breast lumps like fibroadenoma or cysts do appear suspicious on x-rays sometimes,but it's nothing more than that., '12322143211': The fact that the report states that no vasculariry (blood flow)or architectural distortion is present,it's a good sign!, '501432412': Most biopsy are recommended just to make sure and it's an excellent medical procedure to obtain a correct diagnosis!, '763991487': Try not to worry....Hopefully this is nothing to be concerned about., '117037783': Wishing you all the best!, '613740522': Thanks zouzi., '635750617': I don't think it's a cyst because it's not clear, has calcifications in it :/  that's what the radiologist said to me., '643830451': And it has some tapering so not a nice well circumcised lesion, all risk factors for malignancy from what I have read., '1308237156': I feel too young to have cancer., '1102378694': But then I've read that it can happen any age., '1217557325': There's just so many stories of young women who are fighting this that I've read about in the last week on the internet., '829598488': It's make things seem more probable., '502466638':  Whatever the result, this experience has made me realise that I need to change the way I live And live a bit more for today., '830188379': I have never felt so anxious or scared in my life., '1388205763': I'll never take my life for granted again., '1644395052': I'm amazed at how muh this has changed me., '1361474653': Yes,I know that the possibility of "breast cancer" can cause a lot of stress and anxiety,but remember that reading stories over the internet about women with BC is not necessarily related to your situation at all,since you haven't been diagnosed with anything yet., '3423432342': Try your best to stay calm and don't let your mind be filled with negative thoughts., '1864889785': Keep in mind that many breast lumps are not cancerous,even suspicious ones... and I hope the same for you too., '565692068': Please let us know when you receive your biopsy results and lets hope for a favorable outcome., '1,43321E+12': Take care.., '1082473215': Ok I'll let you know, '593723525': I just had a look to the sonographers report and she wrote cystic and solid components present with calcifications., '1521007404': That's a good thing right?, '113200225': Ok thanks., '1606383588': Yeah what's happened is I have a copy of what the sonographer wrote, and the final report of what the radiologist wrote., '820742501': This is where there are different descriptions., '1809439220': Sonopgrapher wrote cystic and solid components but the final report has what I wrote originally., '1494162804': Even I'm confused as to who is correct!, '561727243': I just responded to your private message., '1366852053': What are the chances treating this type of cancer with radiation only?, '742347649':  Does the statistics change any and if so, can you tell me the percentage!, '581873026': I recently under went a lumpectomy in July, I also has lymph nodes involved., '125054595': The tumors were removed, my margins came back clear., '836067605': I don't want to go through chemotherapy, I am willing to do radiation along with hepercin  will this  help me at all?, '1863446660': I think what the doctor is trying to tell you is that surgery in your case is necessary, and which you now say you had., '2004562029': He also said that especially if lymph nodes are involved, chemotherapy is highly recommended and the right way to go in your case., '1961621684': It will not guarantee that you will live forever but it will increase your chances of living longer., '37032338': I do understand what you are saying, after all mt tests from the muga scan to the mri bone scat and cat scan., '481548035': Blood work and so on, after all the tests came back would the doctors know if the cance has spresd to other area outside of my lymph nodes?, '72493': Hi., '103258448':  If the cancer has been found in the lymph nodes, there is a significant probability that there is already microscopic spread to other areas of the body., '595987251':  This microscopic spread may not be easily detected by conventional imaging procedures., '669179545':  So even if the initial tests were negative for distant metastases, if the lymph nodes are already involved, it is imperative to do some additional treatment like chemotherapy, since we are not sure that the negative results are totally reliable., '1176941028': Is there a time lime to have chemotherapy?,, '581871935': right now I am unable to have the chemotherapy due to financial reason., '1720485447': I am not counting it out all together maybe sometime next year?, '2016512704': This is what I have been told., '1934410799': When you are first diagnosed, a team of doctors set up your treatment plan. (, '1154697713': or a doctor/doctors talk about what they think is the best thing to do in any particular case for the best possible outcome and prevention of reoccurrence.), '138194740': Then , if the patient agrees to this, you go ahead with it., '1201545935': If you do, then the initial treatments are really the most important of all the treatment, as the goal is to wipe out whatever cancer there is and may be lurking the very first time., '1597602703': If you decide to do chemo a year or so later, this will no longer be part of the initially recommended treatment that according to the doctor's best judgement has the highest chance of working in your best interest., '1893726723': Radiation will certainly help with reoccurrence, and it will attack whatever may have spread outside of the surgical area that was removed., '1925896154': But as the doctor above explains, with positive lymph nodes there is a chance that the cancer has spread, and in half of the cases those lesions are so tiny that they won't show up on a bone scan or other test., '44162754': So, this is why chemotherapy is utilized to make sure that if this spread is there it is wiped out by chemo immediately, because after the first chance the cancer will only spread and grow. (, '1432263948': I mean even with radiation, it will grow outside of the radiation area.), '154584627': Radiation is local treatment just like surgery, and chemo is systemic., '1690568799': So is tamoxifen but  it's not indicated in your case., '28363907': Do not put off chemo because of financial reasons., '225524585': There are breast cancer advocate organizations that can help you get treatment., '177959985': I think one of them is called youcanthrive.org, or something close to that., '185245756': Find an advocate and get the treatment you need., '664344341': Your LIFE is more important than financial considerations., '768772863': NOBODY in this country should have to risk recurrence of a life threatening disease because they can't afford treatment., '813046622': I had Stage 3 Invasive Ductal Carcinoma in 09., '433206050': Treatment included 2 lumpectomies, chemotherapy and radiation., '2085510238': When cancer reaches your lymph nodes, you have no idea where the cancer cells have traveled through your body, therefore chemotherapy treatment is necessary., '765918576': Do you know of any more of the advocate and financial support groups?, '867686277': Thank you., '1965985106': 4 1/2 years ago my mother has a cancerous lump taken out of her breast., '1609572357': SHE DID NO TREATMENTs., '929515175': About a year ago she found another lump in the same breast but this time on the outside., '1213276660': She found a doctor that has been treating it., '1106332463': we thought it was getting better., '1986504846': Just a couple of months ago the same doctor who is in another state where we live ordered a bone scan her at home., '716640418': The results according to this doctor weren't good., '950190958': He said there was nothing else he could do., '1092436990': We found a cancer doctor here at home., '1270390595': It is now in her lymph notes under her arm and in her chest and she also has another lump in the same breast inside again., '1473977741': It has been growing since her surgery 4 1/2 years ago., '832528475': This doctor said it is not in any of her organs ., '1572601787': All the natural stuff my mom was taking saved her organs., '539281426': It is in her bones now., '1028754948': The doctor here will have them in a week., '1813513923': It only will be than that he will know what bones and how many the cancer is now in., '1621380010': Is it true once it reaches the bones it is stage 4?, '1444913828': What can we expect, She also starts chemo in one week., '1697662502': I'm so sorry to learn of your Mother's present condition., '642253599': Evidently she received very poor medical care when her first cancer was discovered., '488223791': The fact that she now has metastisis to the bone isn't the main issue as bone mets is quite easliy managed., '1408161443': The lymph node involvement is the problem to be addressed first., '196054867': I truly hope that you are being treated by an Oncologist and that she will not refuse whatever treatment that is recommended., '1385510409': The only proven treatment for cancer at any stage is a combination of Chemotherapy, Radiation and possible Hormone Therapy following the appropriate surgery at the time the cancer is first discovered., '1407088066': As far as prognosis at this point; that would be something you should discuss with your Mother's Oncologist as he/she has all the necessary information regarding the cancer., '1948393844':   Kindest regards ..., '1788922570': So sorry to learn of your mother's health.... The first doctor apparently did not do his job aty all., '1928664350':  By all means, seek the assistance of a good oncologist -- but listen to his/her recommendations., '907659569':  They will almost always without a doubt recommend the chemotherapy protocol, which has NOT been proven to help the majority of those receiving it (less than 15%)., '560199523':  Remember one thing -- and that is an oncologist job is to educate and inform patients only of what they are taught and told to relate to patients., '485802373':   Please do your research for your mother -- it can save her life and give her peace of mind as well as quality of life., '444804405':  My prayers are with you., '234035479': I've only gotten 2 responses to my post which either tell me there is something someone does't want to tell me or my concerns aren't enough., '107747505': Thanks for nothing, '2136337468': I am so sorry to hear about your mother's health., '1571405929':  I can certainly appreciate your concern and your wish to get concrete answers., '1381760063':  I am in a similar position having been recently diagnosed with metastases to the bones., '1480289459':  From what I understand this means that the cancer is in stage IV., '539257107':  Information on the computer suggests that mets to the bone and not to the vital organs are considered the "best"., '106241957':  My doctor said that she has seen a few patients live for 10 years in this condition., '1605567116':  The danger is that the cancer will move to vital organs., '795795600':  If you look on the computer the statistics for life with metastatic cancer are grim (2-3yrs)  I have been assured that life expectancy can be much longer if the cancer can be stabilized., '484806445':  I am hoping that this will be true for me and I definitely hope that this will be true for your mother., '1532571418':  I hope that this is somewhat helpful., '1730111321':  I don't think any one, cancer patient or oncologist, is quick to put a life expectancy in absolute terms., '2091039161':  I do understand, however, the wish to have certainty in such a vulnerable situation., '671102709':  Best wishes, jonji, '2042319386': I'm sorry you felt that your concerns were not answered., '537245091': I re-read your original post and found the only question to be "was bone mets considered Stage 4" .. Obviously your mother either refused treatment when she was first diagnosed and this is certainly the main reaosn for the recurrance., '1293842950': Natural remedies DO NOT prevent or cure breast cancer., '1944325208': As I mentioned before, bone mets can be managed quite well and there are many Stage IV women who alive and living with the bone mets., '1017199364':  If you would like some information from some of those Stage IV survivors you might visit the following website which is a discussion group and there are some amazing women there who are more than willing to share their experiences as Stage IV Survivors., '1686272538': Your Mother's Oncologist remains the best source of information regarding her particular case., '1682013220': Ck., '307667135': out this website though if you have time: bcsupport.org, '53793552': I am so sorry you got another diagnosis of cancer., '557143313': I am sending prayers your way that you get the correct treatment and that you recover again., '1688203622':  And I'm sorry you've had a tough time posting., '17213397': I value your posts and I believe other women do as well., '2067631457': I ran into the same issue and I was fortunate to get a moderator who allowed me to explain why I post about BRCA and use a certain website for women to get more information., '1539200246': I was given an opportunity to share all of the research available there and they saw that it was of value to the people who visit medhelp., '1354462820': Apparently it's against their terms of service, something about competing sites., '1722434218': I do understand why you would offer that website to someone desperate for information and I know your heart is in the right place., '1845839047': We advocate for women with breast cancer., '941658061': We try to help however we can., '1616326558': Even if it's just a cyber hug. (, '314388362': You may want to check into the PARP inhibitor studies going on right now for metastatic breast cancer.), '469037742':   My thoughts and prayers are with you., '2198965472': Best wishes., '562847482': hi i am new to this website and responding but just had to with yours i had BC diagnosed 2006, bone mets stage 1V in june 2008, i have oestrogen receptive bc and was put on letrozole, i have jsut had a bone scan and have a few more bone mets adn so have changed to another aromatase inhibitor  but hey thats 3 yrs and i have been great so fingers crossed heres to another 3 yrs before i have to change drugs again., '1552065150': so keep positive xx, '1441703498': absolutly DO NOT TAKE FENTYNAL PATCHES!, '1220822976': i am 36 years old and i had breast cancer to they gave me fentynal., '492847186': i regret ever taking it it has ruined my life!, '1496108920': DO NOT TAKE!, '741971521': This drug is really only meant for the terminally ill!, '174555518': Its the most horrible pain medicine to come off of., '1256911902': I was not addicted to it and had no idea I was going on the strongest pain medicine in the world., '1464137185': It is 100x stronger than morphine and 50 x stronger than herion., '673528659': It causes all kinds of side effects., '2028780393': I had a friend on it for 3 weeks and she wanted to die when she was tapering off of it., '14807202': This drug is hell and is not worth it., '65041780': Stay away!, '1028282054': You will thank me!, '450062941': I had to learn the HARD way!, '1169452023': Hi, I suggest you go to a pain management group., '1185961405':  There are lots of options., '1772157998':  My wife was stage 4 and tried all options., '731582607':  She wasn't able to handle any pain medicine except for darvicet., '1168179321':  My rub down and long car rides were her main source of relief., '181626204':  Please see an expert on pain management., '523196775':  No drug is bad if it keep you from having pain., '738076907': All my best., '2051161520': Kemal, '1784163674': I have been on the fentanyl patch for a year now - I have not had one problem with it!, '297670020':  My pain is caused from Stage 4 BC with mets to the bones and lungs., '422945684':  I am still using the patch -  175 mcg's every 3 days plus oxycodone - 6 to 8 a day plus doing the chemo (chemo for 3 years)., '1131396203':  I have not had any side effects and am pleased with how the patch is working!!, '1656634257': I have been on varying doses over the Fentanyl patch for 3+ years &amp; am currently trying to slowly taper down., '720930665': I've tried this a few times before &amp; EVERY time the withdrawals are so severe that I end up hospitalized &amp; once even on life support., '1138607008': This time has been absolute hell &amp; I STRONGLY urge that NO ONE uses this DRUG !!!, '121933810': I was not told by my dr when it was prescribed how bad it was &amp; I couldn't find any information online., '732335755': Within a week of starting it I could feel the difference &amp; everyone around me could see differences in me., '1330946708': I HAVE NEVER ABUSED THE DRUG, take it EXACTLY as prescribed &amp; still have a dependence to them., '980988051': I'd LOVE to come off them, but at this time am pregnant &amp; to try &amp; come off now is pretty much a death sentence for both of us., '905034152': I have been pregnant before on this horrible drug &amp; did carry to term., '1385244267': She went through 2 weeks in the NICU with withdrawals which were the HARDEST 2 weeks of my life., '1225833392': She is a happy &amp; healthy above average 2 yr old who loves everything., '1851510828': I pray every night that this child I am carrying is healthy &amp; pray that he'll do ok., '159705254': I'm withdrawaling pretty bad right now due to a miscalculation by my dr so right now I can SAFELY tell you that NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO YOU WILL BECOME ACCUSTOM TO THESE HORRID PATCHES &amp; WILL GO THROUGH WITHDRAWALS., '2022963556': I don't want to see anyone suffer this if I can prevent it so PLEASE STAY AWAY FROM THEM !!!!!!!!!!}}
